Lee Rigby's son has penned a touching tribute to the murdered soldier as a memorial to mark his 'ultimate sacrifice' has been unveiled in his hometown.

Family and friends of the 25-year-old, gathered for a dedication service at Middleton Memorial Gardens where a bronze drum and a plaque in his honour went on public display.

His four-year-old son, Jack, was among those attending the ceremony in Greater Manchester, and together with his mother, Rebecca,  laid a floral tribute at the memorial with a message reading: 'Me and Mummy Miss and Love You lots and lots. Jack xxx.'

