Fusilier Rigby - a drummer and machine gunner with the 2nd Battalion Royal Regiment of Fusiliers - was killed outside his barracks in Woolwich, south-east London, in May 2013 by two Islamic extremists. 

British-born Muslim converts Michael Adebolajo, 29, and Michael Adebowale, 23, ran Fusilier Rigby down in a car before hacking him to death with a meat cleaver and knives in a frenzied attack in Woolwich, south London.

They dumped the body of the father-of-one in the middle of the road near Woolwich Barracks in south east London on May 22 2013.

